The paper addresses the problem of efficient exploration for learning lifted operators in sequential decision-making problems without extrinsic goals or rewards, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a general method for exploration, which involves planning to achieve specific, targeted effects in the world, which is related to machine learning and planning, and thus cs.LG and cs.PL are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the benefits of the proposed method in domains with long horizons, which is related to robotics and control, and thus cs.RO and cs.SY are also possible sub-categories.
